r error mapping\\n\\n## Requirements Met\\n\\n✅ New endpoint at correct path: `POST /api/applications/:id/manual-review`  \\n✅ Route placed in `app/backend/src/routes/applications.ts`  \\n✅ Orchestration logic in `app/backend/src/services/loan-service.ts`  \\n✅ Business logic NOT in route handler  \\n✅ Only `analyst-manager` role allowed  \\n✅ Delegated sessions rejected with FORBIDDEN error  \\n✅ Loan lifecycle status NOT changed  \\n✅ Emits `notification.requested` broker event  \\n✅ Event uses `event: \\\"manual-review-escalation\\\"`  \\n✅ No new queue contract types added  \\n✅ Existing audit pattern used with action name `loan.manual-review-requested`  \\n✅ Response payload matches spec: `{ ok, applicationId, notificationEventId }`  \\n✅ California high-risk rule implemented correctly  \\n✅ Feature flag checked before applying CA prefix  \\n\\n## Compliance with Repo Conventions\\n\\n- Uses TypeScript strict mode\\n- Uses ESM imports\\n- Route handlers pass errors to `next()`\\n- Mutating operation audited via broker and audit service\\n- Domain types imported from `models/types.ts`\\n- Business logic in service layer\\n- Follows error prefix pattern (FORBIDDEN, NOT_FOUND, etc.)\\n- Central error handler maps errors to HTTP status codes\\n- Delegated session restrictions enforced\\n\"}",
